# PRAXIS Pipeline, Eval & Integration Guidelines

## Python & Data Contracts
- All Python modules: strict typing, Google-style docstrings, and explicit data contracts between distillation, clustering, scoring, and dashboard API responses.
- Provenance fields mandatory on every candidate/lesson object (source log path + line offset).
- Eval harness outputs must include before/after correction counts, tokens, time, plus compounding curve data for dashboard consumption.

## Integration Points (Days 6-7)
- Dashboard ↔ backend: REST/GraphQL endpoints return full provenance + confidence breakdown; approval mutations trigger GitHub hook/PR creation (Dominic).
- Knowledge injection: generated CLAUDE.md / skills include only promoted items with decay rules applied; expose injection logs for eval measurement.

## Measurement & Demo Readiness
- Fixed quirky repo tasks + metrics defined early (Day 2); cold-run baseline captured before any injection.
- Day 8: full compounding curve measurement; identify and handle demo quirks.
- Use `fix-ci` and `loop-on-ci` once GitLab CI is live; keep harness deterministic for credible ≥50% improvement proof.

These ensure the architecture/eval pillar produces measurable, reproducible results that back the team narrative.